      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Crush the {{digestive-biscuits}} to fine crumbs, in a food processor or in a sealed bag with a rolling pin. Mix with the melted {{unsalted-butter}} until the crumbs are evenly dampened. Press into the base of the springform tin in an even layer. Refrigerate while you make the filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{full-fat-cream-cheese}} and {{icing-sugar}} together until smooth. In a separate bowl, whip the 300 ml of {{double-cream}} with the {{vanilla-extract}} to soft peaks: the cream should hold its shape when you lift the beaters but the tips should curl over rather than stand upright. Fold the whipped cream into the cream cheese in three additions.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Swirl in dulce de leche",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the 200 g of {{dulce-de-leche}} and fold it through the filling with just three or four strokes, enough to create a ripple, not to blend it evenly. Spoon onto the biscuit base and smooth the top. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours, overnight if possible.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Top before serving",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Run a warm knife around the inside of the tin before unclipping. Arrange the sliced {{bananas}} over the top, spoon or pipe the lightly whipped cream over the banana, and drizzle over the extra {{dulce-de-leche}} if using. Serve immediately or within 2 hours.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
